hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Write the trace:
$$
H = g^{\mu\nu}H_{\mu\nu}
   = 2\,g^{\mu\nu}A_{\mu\nu} \;-\;\tfrac12\,g^{\mu\nu}g_{\mu\nu}\,\mathcal{G}.
$$
2. Compute each contraction:
$$
g^{\mu\nu}A_{\mu\nu}
= g^{\mu\nu}\bigl(RR_{\mu\nu}
   -2R_{\mu\rho}R^{\rho}{}_{\nu}
   -2R_{\mu\rho\nu\sigma}R^{\rho\sigma}
   +R_{\mu\rho\sigma\delta}R_{\nu}{}^{\rho\sigma\delta}\bigr)
$$
gives
$$
R^2-2R_{\mu\nu}R^{\mu\nu}-2R_{\mu\nu}R^{\mu\nu}+R_{\mu\rho\sigma\delta}R^{\mu\rho\sigma\delta}
=R^2-4R_{\mu\nu}R^{\mu\nu}+R_{\mu\rho\sigma\delta}R^{\mu\rho\sigma\delta}
=\mathcal{G}.
$$
3. Insert back:
$$
H = 2\mathcal{G}-\tfrac12D\,\mathcal{G} = \frac{4-D}{2}\,\mathcal{G}.
$$
